  Guardian ad Litem license renewal may be completed in the MyBoardAccess p
 ortal from July 1 through August 31\, 2026 at 5:00 pm.\n+ Pursuant to M. B
 ar R. 4\,\n+ Registration documents and payments received after August 31s
 t will be assessed a non-waivable late fee.\n+ We greatly appreciate your 
 updated contact information\, proxy\, and IOLTA account listing\, and serv
 ice email for court service and notices.\n+ If your status has changed sin
 ce last year:\n+ new law clerk\n+ clerkship ended or is ending soon\n+ ret
 ired seeking to be Inactive\n+ new judge\n+ no longer a judge\n+ active mi
 litary or changing status\n+ seeking to become active again\n+ Before you 
 register in the portal\, please contact\n+ execassistant@mebaroverseers.or
 g\n+ to request a status change.\n+ Please note\, if you still owe a CLE l
 ate fee your license renewal/registration cannot be approved until that is
  resolved.\n+ Registration is completed online on the\n+ MyBoardAccess\n+ 
 by clicking on the Renew Registration section of the Board's web portal. A
  confirmation email will automatically be sent to you from informe.org whe
 n your registration is approved.\n+ 7/1/2026\n+ In re: Felix R. Hagenimana
